{
  "stem": "3085.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I mean, it was no bed of roses.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But relatively speaking, we were much better off than Jews in, say, Poland or, or Czechoslovakia or, or the Baltic states.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There's no question about it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We did not-- I certainly did not know, but I don't think my parents knew at the time what went-- what went on in-- on in Poland and, and-- about concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I understand-- well, this of course came out after the war-- the Kastner Affair that you must have heard about, when Rudolf Kastner was accused of not telling the Hungarian Jewry about things that apparently he knew about.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I-- you know, I don't want to take sides in that issue.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But, but the fact is that Hungarian Jews and, certainly, Jews in, in the provinces other than the capital, were quite ignorant about what was going on in, in Poland with the Jews in, in Nazi-occupied Europe and other places like in the Baltic states.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And by the time I think they realized, it was too late.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] My father, till today, I think, he feels guilty about it.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "He's got a tremendous guilt for not doing something about it when there was still time to do something about it.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But I can't blame him.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "He didn't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "He-- the, the, the, the-- we were-- we were assimilated Jews.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Certainly, that part of Hungary, the part that's called Transdanubia, most Jews were pretty assimilated to the Hungarian population and Hungarian culture.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "My father was actually an officer in the First World War in the Hungarian-- Austro-Hungarian Army and fought, of course, on the side of Hungary against the Allies.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Hungary always had a knack of joining the wrong side in history.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "It's a-- it's a tremendous knack.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
